# List-page CRUD

Canonical pattern: **`useXListPage` + `XListPage`**. Mirror `src/features/users/`. Do not invent parallel dialog stacks or put fetch/modals in the route file.

## Shape

1. Hook: load via `useError().run(listX())`; keep `load()` for post-mutation refresh
2. Hook: gate with `can(me.role, Actions.<feature>.write)` (or `.read` for read-only lists)
3. Hook: Create/Edit → `openModal({ type: "form", … })` + dirty bridge + `run` + `applyServerErrors` + toast + `closeModal` + `load()`
4. Hook: Delete → `confirm({ variant: "destructive" })` → `run(deleteX(id))` → toast + `load()`
5. View: render `DynamicTable` / empty / loading from props; build toolbar/row UI from `canWrite` + callbacks
6. Route: `const page = useXListPage(); return <XListPage {...page} />` inside the table shell wrapper
7. Empty state still shows Create when `canWrite`. Lists are full arrays — DynamicTable pages client-side only
8. Do not add `[id]` detail routes or orphan `getX(id)` unless the task asks for them

```ts
const canWrite = me ? can(me.role, Actions.users.write) : false

await authorize(Actions.users.write) // server actions only
```

## Imports

| Need | From |
|------|------|
| Hook | `features/<f>/hooks/use-*-list-page` |
| View | `features/<f>/components/pages/*-list-page` |
| Table | `@/components/shared/table/dynamic-table` |
| Modals | `@/components/shared/modals` → `useModal` (in the **hook**) |
| Errors | `@/features/errors` → `useError` (in the **hook**) |
| RBAC UI | `@/features/auth/permissions` → `Actions`, `can` |
| Auth me | `@/features/auth/hooks/use-auth` |

Never import `@/features/auth/session` or `@/features/errors/server` from hooks/views/routes.

## App route

Client page under `src/app/(app)/…/page.tsx` that wires hook → view (full-bleed table-shell wrapper as in team/members).

See `.docs/components/list-pages.md` and `.docs/components/architecture.md`.
